      </li>
      
      <li class="ctsh clearfix" data-cid="38330379">
        <div class="ilst">
          <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/wanwanranran/"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u44218741-163.jpg" alt="Aurora的🐱" class="" /></a>
        </div>
        <div class="con">
          <div class="nlst">
            <h3>
              <div class="note-toggle rr">
                <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/38330379/" class="note-unfolder">展开</a>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="note-folder">收起</a>
              </div>
              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/38330379/" class="">第107页</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/wanwanranran/" class=" " title="Aurora的🐱">Aurora的🐱</a>
                (ฅ՞•ﻌ•՞ฅ)
              
                <span class="allstar10" title="很差"></span>
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="38330379">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">Jens Westemeier书中每章后面都附有许多notes，起初以为他真的很严谨地在做一个黑呢，心想也算此人唯一一点优点了吧。

没想到啊没想到……仔细看注释，原来还能这样？【doge】



比如主观臆测的——

The Panzer Regiment stood up for formation. In front of black SS flags, and framed by Panther tanks, SS-Obersturmbannfuhrer Joachim Peiper gave a speech to his men, most likely full of typical NS and SS p...</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2016-07-28 23:40</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                Jens Westemeier书中每章后面都附有许多notes，起初以为他真的很严谨地在做一个黑呢，心想也算此人唯一一点优点了吧。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>没想到啊没想到……仔细看注释，原来还能这样？【doge】<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>比如主观臆测的——<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>The Panzer Regiment stood up for formation. In front of black SS flags, and framed by Panther tanks, SS-Obersturmbannfuhrer Joachim Peiper gave a speech to his men, most likely full of typical NS and SS platitudes as could be found in Leibstandarte propaganda: &quot;We want to be the best...because people expect this performance from us, and must expect it.&quot;<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>(20 The original speech is not recorded. SS veterans especially recall that Peiper normally praised Adolf Hitler in speeches, and mentioned to fulfill the obligation of wearing the name Adolf Hitler on their cuff title. Interview with Dr. Arndt Fischer and Rolf Reiser on 04/24/1996. The quote above is from a &quot;weekly political newsreel of the Leibstandarte&quot; November 1944 as quoted in Weingartner: &quot;Hitler's Guard.&quot; p. 141.) <div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>EXM？？ 没有原始讲话，不知从哪里找一篇，然后就给人扣个陈词滥调的帽子？？这也行？？？？┻━┻︵╰(‵□′)╯︵┻━┻<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>&quot;I recognize that after the battle of Normandy my unit was composed mainly of young, fanatical soldiers. A good deal of them had lost parents, sisters, and brothers during the bombing. They had seen for themselves in Cologne thousands of mangled corpses after a terror raid had passed. Their hatred for the enemy was such, I swear it, I could not always keep it under control.&quot;<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>（23c Joachim Peiper, cited from Reynold's &quot;Devil's Adjutant,&quot; p. 36. Maybe this was an indication that many SS men were looking forward to exacting revenge on the Americans.）<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>你们就这样互相引用？OK~对地摊界要求不能太高~ 但是这种自带maybe的假设也可以当注释吗？？？太不负责了吧！<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>还有貌似他确实采访到很多人，但只要一言不合（或者生前没配合讲你派坏话）出现在注释里就会是这样的形象——<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>SS-Gruppenführer Hermann Prieß (05/24/1901-02/02/1985) joined the NSDAP No. 1.472.296 as a &quot;March violet&quot; (SS No. 113.258) in March 1933. Prieß fought as a seventeen-year-old volunteer with the Free Corps in the Baltic area. Highly praised by Theodor Eicke as &quot;unusually reliable&quot; and &quot;unspoiled,&quot; Prieß led the SS Totenkopf Division, and won the Swords to the Knight's Cross. Seen as a commander of &quot;iron will and inner hardness,&quot; at the same time, it was suggested, that he needed an intelligent assistant! By October 24, 1944, he became Commander 1 SS Panzer Corps. Sentenced in the Malmedy Trial, Prieß was released from the Landsberg War Criminal prison by 1954. For more on Prieß, see also Sydnor: &quot;Soldaten des lodes&quot; and Weingartner: &quot;Crossroads,&quot; p. 32.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>哈哈哈哈 Kumm这个真笑死我了XDDD<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Communication Otto Kumm to the author February 1993. SS-Brigadeführer Otto Kumm (10/01/1909-02/23/2004) stayed in close contact with Peiper after the war. and worked hard with the HIAG to paint a &quot;glorious&quot; pure soldier image of the Waffen-SS. Kumm. the last commander of the Leibstandarte, joined the SS in 1931 (SSNo. 18.727, NSDAP No. 421.230), and remained a convinced Nazi to his death.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>嗯，Otto Kumm是一个在战后与派普保持密切联系，并与HIAG努力营造一个“光荣”的纯粹的武装党卫军军人形象的死NZ。嗯。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Interview with Rudolf v. Ribbentrop on 03/27/1993. Also a report from v. Ribbentrop in Lehmann: &quot;Vol. Ⅲ&quot; p. 200. For a different image of Peiper see ie the statements from Albert Frey to Charles Whiting. Only few veterans openly critiqued the life-disdaining leadership style of some SS commanders in the I. SS Panzer Corps in interviews with the author, most remaining anonymous. <div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>SS-Hauplsturmfuhrer Rudolf von Ribbentrop (05/11/1921), son of the German Foreign Minister, volunteered lor the SS (No. 4(X). 121) by 1939. Having been with the SS Kampfgruppe Nord in Salla in 1941, he came to the Tank regiment of the Leibstandarte by 1942. Ribbentrop was transferred to the 12th SS Panzer Division &quot;Hitlerjugend,&quot; and became commander of a scrambled Panzer Battalion there in 1945. After the war, he made his career with a well known German bank corporation. He stayed in close contact with his former comrades, and contributed to division chronicles with reports.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>貌似大公子也没说啥，与老战友保持联系协助写师战史J.W也不满意？<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>噢，J.W满意的受访者是这样的：<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Interview with Herbert Walther on 05/25/1994. SS-Untersturmführer Herbert Waither (04/23/1922-02/05/2003) fought with the SS divisions &quot;Leibstandarte&quot; and &quot;Hitlerjugend.&quot; Waller was an extremely popular oddball, loved social gatherings with his old SS comrades, but hated the worshipping of former SS commanders, especially Max Wünsche and Joachim Peiper, as he made them directly responsible tor the death of numerous men due to their style of command. Walther worked with the Federal Archive in Koblenz after the war, and published several SS photo books. See ie Walther, Herbert: The Waffen-SS. Schiffer Publishing. Atglen 1989<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div> ……especially Max Wünsche and Joachim Peiper（说黑遍德三的J.W唯独赞赏温舍的，你们YY的开心就好23333<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>P.S. 不止107页。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>对J.W的吐槽暂时到此为止吧。我还有好多书要看呢~<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>
